			<ns0:name>sa...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/111227428049549265840/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Each time there is a change to the trusted or shared code base, there should be an integration that runs the latest build of Chromium.  The test should start the browser and point to a test html file which would load the NaCl plugin and run a nexe binary (e.g. hello_world).  Browser interaction would be driven by selenium.

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Currently there are no integrations tests that run a nexe appliction

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
We have no way of tracking if the entire system is broken, or tracking the last known good combinations of NaCl and Chrome revisions.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Add functionality to the builds to grab a specific version of Chromium and run selenium tests with the latest builds of NaCl plugin and a nexe from the current version of toolchain specified in the DEPS file.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
Integration tests for Windows, linux, and OS X and results are displayed on http://goto/naclbot

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
Failing integration tests would turn the tree red.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-06-13T18:08:05.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-01-05T21:44:56.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
